			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Total Suspended Particles (TSP) are microscopic particles of solid or liquid matter suspended in the air. The units of measure are micrograms per cubic meter of air (µg/m3). The National Ambient Air Quality Standards (NAAQS) for particulate matter, first established in 1971, were based on TSP with an aerodynamic diameter of 100 micrograms per cubic meter (μg/m 3) or less. Sometimes the term 'suspended matter' is used. Measurements of TSP are replaced by measurements of PM10 and PM2.5, because the limit values now refer to these yardsticks for particle concentrations.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">总悬浮颗粒 (TSP) 是悬浮在空气中的固体或液体物质的微小颗粒。测量单位为每立方米空气中的微克数（µg/m3）。1971 年首次制定的《国家环境空气质量标准》（NAAQS）的颗粒物标准是基于空气动力学直径为 100 微克/立方米（μg/m 3）或更小的 TSP。有时也使用 &quot;悬浮物 &quot;一词。对 TSP 的测量被 PM10 和 PM2.5 的测量所取代，因为现在的限值就是指这些颗粒浓度的标准。</common:generalComment>
